        "segment": "status:-free",
        "alignment": "left",
        "html": "<p><em><strong>Friends:</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>Yesterday, I learned that I am a </strong></em><a href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/david-sirota-dont-look-up-2022-oscars-nomination-1235088370/\"><em><strong>nominee for an Academy Award</strong></em></a><em><strong> in the best original screenplay category for my work on the film </strong></em><strong>Don’t Look Up</strong><em><strong>. The fact that the film, a climate allegory, has achieved such critical and popular success is a testament to the growing demand for efforts that buck corporate media narratives and challenge power. I am stunned and truly grateful for this Oscar nomination. Thanks to your support, you are helping us respond to that demand </strong>— <strong>so thank you, once again, for being a paying subscriber. You deserve part of the credit for this wonderful honor.</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>Rock the boat,</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>Sirota</strong></em></p>"
      }
